      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's Coach Wanderley Luxemburgo is planning changes for Brazil's World Cup qualifying game in Paraguay (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brazil's Coach Wanderley Luxemburgo is planning more changes for Brazil's World Cup qualifying game in Paraguay today. Luxemburgo is expected to make at least five changes from the lineup that struggled in a 1-1 tie with Uruguay last month at home. Luxemburgo is expected to play Sao Paulo's Edmilson and Palmeiras' Roque Junior in an untried central defensive partnership, and field a five-man midfield.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Brazil's Coach Wanderley Luxemburgo is planning more changes for Brazil's World Cup qualifying game in Paraguay today. Luxemburgo is expected to make at least five changes from the lineup that struggled in a 1-1 tie with Uruguay last month at home. Luxemburgo is expected to play Sao Paulo's Edmilson and Palmeiras' Roque Junior in an untried central defensive partnership, and field a five-man midfield.</p>
        <p>The match between Brazil and Paraguay in Asuncion is one of five South American qualifiers being played this week. Uruguay will also play host to Venezuela today, with two matches to be played tomorrow. Colombia will visit Peru and Chile will visit Bolivia, while Argentina will play host to Ecuador on Saturday.</p>
        <p>ALEX YANNIS</p>
        <p>SOCCER: NOTEBOOK</p>
      </block>
